full_text: This might seem small and insignificant, but it's huge to me.
full_text(utf-8): b"This might seem small and insignificant, but it's huge to me."

full_text: When I start feeling guilty for feeling happy, or I start to feel unworthy of the joy that's bubbling inside, I make myself stop and remind myself that I'm worthy of good things and that what I'm feeling is okay.
full_text(utf-8): b"When I start feeling guilty for feeling happy, or I start to feel unworthy of the joy that's bubbling inside, I make myself stop and remind myself that I'm worthy of good things and that what I'm feeling is okay."

full_text: My therapist has challenged me to lean into the joy and I'm trying my hardest.
full_text(utf-8): b"My therapist has challenged me to lean into the joy and I'm trying my hardest."

full_text: Trying out a new recipe makes my heart smile.
full_text(utf-8): b'Trying out a new recipe makes my heart smile.'

full_text: And the things I'm finding pleasure in aren't huge things. Taking 10 minutes in the morning to sit in silence and enjoy a cup of tea is joy. Standing on my balcony and just breathing brings me pleasure.
full_text(utf-8): b"And the things I'm finding pleasure in aren't huge things. Taking 10 minutes in the morning to sit in silence and enjoy a cup of tea is joy. Standing on my balcony and just breathing brings me pleasure."

full_text: I've decided that being happy isn't a bad thing. God isn't displeased because I'm finding pleasure in life. In fact, I think God wants me to feel good things.
full_text(utf-8): b"I've decided that being happy isn't a bad thing. God isn't displeased because I'm finding pleasure in life. In fact, I think God wants me to feel good things."

full_text: But I've been giving myself the space to truly feel joy and pleasure....and it feels good. Still a little foreign, but good.
full_text(utf-8): b"But I've been giving myself the space to truly feel joy and pleasure....and it feels good. Still a little foreign, but good."

full_text: Pleasure felt....wrong.
full_text(utf-8): b'Pleasure felt....wrong.'

full_text: I was used to operating from a place of anxiety and chaos that joy felt foreign.
full_text(utf-8): b'I was used to operating from a place of anxiety and chaos that joy felt foreign.'

full_text: For the longest I didn't allow myself to really feel things. I didn't feel like joy and pleasure were attainable. Part of me didn't feel like I deserved to feel good things.
full_text(utf-8): b"For the longest I didn't allow myself to really feel things. I didn't feel like joy and pleasure were attainable. Part of me didn't feel like I deserved to feel good things."

full_text: Lately I've been exploring pleasure and joy and what it means to really lean into those feelings. To really allow myself to feel those things.
full_text(utf-8): b"Lately I've been exploring pleasure and joy and what it means to really lean into those feelings. To really allow myself to feel those things."

full_text: Today, I want to encourage you to go deeper. Don’t let ANYTHING stop you from getting into God’s presence. SHOW UP. Don’t hide bits and pieces because you don’t think God can handle it.

full_text: It took a lot of unlearning, a lot of reading, a lot of pushing myself to pray. I had to push past what I thought I knew to learn God in a different way.
full_text(utf-8): b'It took a lot of unlearning, a lot of reading, a lot of pushing myself to pray. I had to push past what I thought I knew to learn God in a different way.'

full_text: And those thoughts created a barrier between me and God. I started building a shallow relationship because I didn’t think I could be 100% me.
full_text(utf-8): b'And those thoughts created a barrier between me and God. I started building a shallow relationship because I didn\xe2\x80\x99t think I could be 100% me.'

full_text: I couldn’t finish my thought because I started spiraling into a really negative headspace. I wondered if God saw the beauty in my relationship, if it made Him sad or mad.
full_text(utf-8): b'I couldn\xe2\x80\x99t finish my thought because I started spiraling into a really negative headspace. I wondered if God saw the beauty in my relationship, if it made Him sad or mad.'

full_text: I didn’t realize how much non-affirming theology and practiced I had internalized until I tried to say the word “girlfriend” during prayer and I was almost paralyzed.

full_text: I felt as if I had to hide the fullness of who I was because it was wrong, I was wrong.
full_text(utf-8): b'I felt as if I had to hide the fullness of who I was because it was wrong, I was wrong.'

full_text: Years of toxic theology and non-affirming religion made it hard for me to give legitimacy to what I was building. It was hard for me have a full and authentic relationship with God.
